author: O k a y y 🥀 D a v i e n
text: Your intuition will aid the creation of your end goal, even if it means knocking that sh*t over and starting again. You doubting your intuition will make you Plateau at some point, and you’ll be stuck watching yourself go no where till you figure it out.

author: O k a y y 🥀 D a v i e n
text: Everyone/thing can be a message from the universe about your idea, it’s up to your intuition to determine if that information can be applied to your personal scenario. Which were all capable of, you just gotta out wit the doubt and keep it pushing.

author: O k a y y 🥀 D a v i e n
text: They helped me understand that even through the doubt I’ve managed to gather the means of creating my idea(s). I just need to put my head down and piece it together.

author: O k a y y 🥀 D a v i e n
text: Therefore I had to start forcing myself to listen to my intuition. So far it’s guided me to to people like @Allergic2Hourly & @sherellesays who’ve helped me understand that what I want is very real and attainable for someone with my background and creative skill set.

author: O k a y y 🥀 D a v i e n
text: After coming to that conclusion I realized that intuition comes before doubt. One wouldn’t doubt themselves if they didn’t have a strong idea in mind or feeling that they gravitate to in the first place.

author: O k a y y 🥀 D a v i e n
text: Then I dug a little deeper and realized that why I doubt myself wasn’t because of me not having or knowing things but because of me subconsciously knowing that the skill set I’m use to won’t make that goal or idea manifest into what I want it to be.

author: O k a y y 🥀 D a v i e n
text: After experiencing some growth, I started asking myself why is it that I’m doubting that I can do something. Or rather why is this doubt making me hesitant. Of course I thought of a long list of things/ reasons I’m without, but that’s my norm so it shouldn’t be that big of a deal

author: O k a y y 🥀 D a v i e n
text: So of course I almost immediately started doubting if I could do it, would I have success, let alone actually understand what it is I’m trying to build.

author: O k a y y 🥀 D a v i e n
text:
—> it just became appealing to you.  

For example in my case, building a business was appealing to me and fits the lifestyle I would like to live. But coming from my background I’ve never once seen one built from the back end to the front.

author: O k a y y 🥀 D a v i e n
text: This year I decided to bet on myself and learn things that’s out of my immediate circle & comfort zone. The uneasiness of committing to something you’ve never seen get accomplished first hand before comes with the territory. Especially if that goal or idea is already attainable->

author: O k a y y 🥀 D a v i e n
text: My biggest take away on the difference would probably be the “why” you never think to ask yourself in real time.
